metadata.description:
CryptoSquare #001/576

A CryptoSquare is a square with 4 rows and 4 columns resulting in 16 tiles in 4 different colors. These 4 rows, 4 columns and 4 colors (blue, green, red and yellow) resulting in over 4 Billion (= 4.294.967.296) possible combinations. Out of these 4+ Billion possibilities,  the CryptoSquares algorithm only found 576 squares containing in each row AND in each column ALL4 different colors. Only these 576 Squares are minted and numbered as CryptoSquares and living on the ethereum blockchain. Have a look and get your favorite number and/or color pattern.

;-)
